1
00:00:00,268 --> 00:00:03,436
[Previously]
Tomorrow will be the last day we're here.

2
00:00:03,436 --> 00:00:07,941
I want to have a date with you at the place where we met for the first time.

3
00:00:07,941 --> 00:00:08,817
Up here on this mountain.

4
00:00:08,817 --> 00:00:10,654
Hey Khun, your hand is burning hot.

5
00:00:10,654 --> 00:00:12,044
This is not okay.

6
00:00:12,044 --> 00:00:13,606
Why didn't you tell me you're sick?

7
00:00:13,606 --> 00:00:14,690
Prince, are you okay?

8
00:00:14,690 --> 00:00:17,205
His body is so cold. He's shivering non-stop.

9
00:00:17,205 --> 00:00:18,090
Is it...

10
00:00:18,090 --> 00:00:18,922
Hey, why are you back here?

11
00:00:18,922 --> 00:00:21,603
If you're looking for antibiotics, I moved them to the other room.

12
00:00:21,603 --> 00:00:23,219
I came to find the medicine to treat Malaria.

13
00:00:23,219 --> 00:00:25,848
If Prince doesn't get treated immediately, he might die.

14
00:00:25,848 --> 00:00:27,172
Look at him.

15
00:00:27,172 --> 00:00:29,263
Let me take care of Prince.

16
00:00:29,263 --> 00:00:33,348
We can clearly see that you can't take care of him at all.

17
00:00:39,820 --> 00:00:43,680
Khru Prince, I bought you and the kids some snacks.

18
00:00:43,680 --> 00:00:45,184
Wow!

19
00:00:45,184 --> 00:00:47,854
- Thank you so much, Loong Phang.
- No problem.

20
00:00:47,854 --> 00:00:50,308
Did you just get back from somewhere?

21
00:00:50,308 --> 00:00:53,792
I went down to pick up the three new volunteers.

22
00:00:53,792 --> 00:01:00,150
Guys, a new volunteer doctor said if we help him clean his house,

23
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:03,140
we will get to play new mobile games.

24
00:01:03,140 --> 00:01:05,574
Oh, Khru Prince.

25
00:01:07,544 --> 00:01:08,840
What did you threaten them with?

26
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:12,219
I just asked them to help me clean up in exchange for some mobile games.

27
00:01:12,219 --> 00:01:17,789
If you came up here just to drink, I think you should go back.

28
00:01:17,789 --> 00:01:20,357
It's true we're here because we did something bad.

29
00:01:20,357 --> 00:01:25,681
But my friend isn't here just to find a place to drink as you thought.

30
00:01:26,930 --> 00:01:32,940
♫ If I must do what my heart tells me ♫

31
00:01:57,401 --> 00:01:59,314
I made it.

32
00:01:59,314 --> 00:02:02,240
It might not be as good as the food in Bangkok. But it's not spicy.

33
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,964
I think you can handle it.

34
00:02:03,964 --> 00:02:06,164
Thank you.

35
00:02:06,164 --> 00:02:08,520
Hello, Dao. It's me, Fah.

36
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:11,226
I borrowed Mesa's phone.

37
00:02:11,226 --> 00:02:13,322
There's no phone signal up here.

38
00:02:13,322 --> 00:02:17,332
I had to walk all over the mountain to get a signal.

39
00:02:20,411 --> 00:02:22,917
Dao, I have to go.

40
00:02:22,917 --> 00:02:24,520
I guess I'm being too loud.

41
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:26,073
The people here must be trying to chase me away.

42
00:02:26,073 --> 00:02:28,750
Sure, okay. Talk to you later.

43
00:02:41,589 --> 00:02:44,590
Prince. Prince.

44
00:02:46,747 --> 00:02:49,817
Prince! Prince!

45
00:02:49,817 --> 00:02:53,850
Finally, you're awake. I was so worried.

46
00:02:53,850 --> 00:02:56,340
Did I…

47
00:02:56,340 --> 00:02:59,656
Prince, you had malaria.

48
00:02:59,656 --> 00:03:00,944
It nearly killed you.

49
00:03:00,944 --> 00:03:07,750
If it wasn't for Sincere who drove you to this hospital, it could have been bad.

50
00:03:16,230 --> 00:03:23,810
[Mek JirakitThawornwong | Mark Jiruntanin Trairattanayon]

51
00:03:23,810 --> 00:03:28,240
♫ Taking a journey, no matter how far the horizon ♫

52
00:03:28,240 --> 00:03:32,960
♫ No matter how high or steep the mountain ♫

53
00:03:32,960 --> 00:03:40,900
♫ But in the end, it's too late, love vanished ♫

54
00:03:40,900 --> 00:03:45,320
♫ Until I met you halfway ♫

55
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:49,820
♫ Just like that, the sky brightened ♫

56
00:03:49,820 --> 00:03:58,800
♫ Don't know why when you're close, it gives me the strength to keep walking ♫

57
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:03,840
♫ Do you think that our love really exists? ♫

58
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:06,850
[Star and Sky│Sky in your heart]

59
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:09,800
[Series Director: Siwat Sawatmaneekul]

60
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:21,310
Drink some water.

61
00:04:22,056 --> 00:04:23,192
You know, Prince?

62
00:04:23,192 --> 00:04:25,231
You slept the whole day.

63
00:04:25,231 --> 00:04:27,871
But you're fine now.

64
00:04:30,269 --> 00:04:33,848
Thank you so much, and…

65
00:04:33,848 --> 00:04:37,501
I'm sorry that I made you worry.

66
00:04:38,592 --> 00:04:40,133
And don't worry about the villagers.

67
00:04:40,133 --> 00:04:42,231
Everyone is doing well now.

68
00:04:42,231 --> 00:04:44,483
You can head home with no concerns.

69
00:04:44,483 --> 00:04:47,417
I heard your new semester is about to start.

70
00:04:47,417 --> 00:04:50,900
What about Dr. Fah?

71
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:52,758
He already left the mountain.

72
00:04:52,758 --> 00:04:56,095
He's probably on his way back to Bangkok now.

73
00:05:01,886 --> 00:05:06,687
I think you should take some rest so you can recover quickly.

74
00:05:25,260 --> 00:05:30,960
Thank you so much, Loong Phang, for driving us all the way here.

75
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:33,747
I should thank you.

76
00:05:33,747 --> 00:05:36,819
If it wasn't for you, my life would be a disaster.

77
00:05:36,819 --> 00:05:39,306
I made you guys grilled pork and sticky rice.

78
00:05:39,306 --> 00:05:40,532
Here. Enjoy.

79
00:05:40,532 --> 00:05:43,220
Thank you.

80
00:05:47,755 --> 00:05:49,829
Yes, Sir?

81
00:05:50,646 --> 00:05:52,506
Khru Prince is conscious now.

82
00:05:52,506 --> 00:05:54,337
Doctor, Khru Prince has awoken.

83
00:05:54,337 --> 00:05:56,990
Can I please talk to the Village Headman?

84
00:05:56,990 --> 00:05:59,790
Sir, Doctor Fah would like to talk to you.

85
00:06:00,533 --> 00:06:02,033
Thank you.

86
00:06:02,775 --> 00:06:04,523
Hello, Village Headman.

87
00:06:04,523 --> 00:06:09,448
Can I please have the name of the hospital Khru Prince is in?

88
00:06:09,448 --> 00:06:14,133
To be honest, Doctor, I'd like to tell you that,

89
00:06:14,133 --> 00:06:20,046
but Sincere asked me not to tell where Khru Prince is.

90
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:22,006
I must apologize.

91
00:06:22,006 --> 00:06:23,706
Okay.

92
00:06:24,797 --> 00:06:26,497
I understand.

93
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:34,297
So? Which hospital?

94
00:06:36,899 --> 00:06:39,600
I don't think we can go.

95
00:06:39,600 --> 00:06:41,900
They said they don't want visitors.

96
00:06:41,900 --> 00:06:43,748
Seriously?

97
00:06:44,781 --> 00:06:46,136
Yes.

98
00:06:46,136 --> 00:06:49,043
And I have work tomorrow.

99
00:06:49,043 --> 00:06:51,377
I can't hang around.

100
00:06:51,377 --> 00:06:54,295
Then I wish you all a safe journey.

101
00:06:54,295 --> 00:06:57,303
Come visit us again.

102
00:06:57,303 --> 00:07:01,481
Sure. When you're home, don't drink too much.

103
00:07:01,481 --> 00:07:06,977
- All right. Goodbye, everyone.
- Goodbye, Loong.

104
00:07:06,977 --> 00:07:08,399
Thank you so much.

105
00:07:08,399 --> 00:07:11,015
- Bye.
- Bye now.

106
00:07:26,220 --> 00:07:28,208
To celebrate your return.

107
00:07:28,208 --> 00:07:30,113
- Cheers!
- Here!

108
00:07:35,475 --> 00:07:37,663
The grilled pork is yummy.

109
00:07:37,663 --> 00:07:39,563
I like it so much.
(T/N: "So much" sounds like "Joong" the name of the actor who plays Kluen)

110
00:07:39,563 --> 00:07:44,249
Right? I told you Loong Phang's pork is superb.

111
00:07:45,011 --> 00:07:47,450
The weather is nice. The food is nice.

112
00:07:47,450 --> 00:07:50,650
I guess you lived comfortably up there.

113
00:07:50,650 --> 00:07:52,700
Not even close.

114
00:07:52,700 --> 00:07:54,181
There's no electricity.

115
00:07:54,181 --> 00:07:55,965
The internet barely worked.

116
00:07:55,965 --> 00:07:58,642
It wasn't just cold. It was freaking cold.

117
00:07:58,642 --> 00:08:02,182
To keep me warm, I almost set myself on fire.

118
00:08:02,182 --> 00:08:07,059
But every time you talk about it, you seem so happy.

119
00:08:07,059 --> 00:08:10,755
Well, it's positive thinking.

120
00:08:10,755 --> 00:08:12,270
I lived up there for so long.

121
00:08:12,270 --> 00:08:17,142
If I hadn't been optimistic, my life would have been miserable.

122
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:27,335
P'Fah, I talked to Dao and decided to go to Germany with friends next week.

123
00:08:27,335 --> 00:08:29,394
Are you interested in joining us?

124
00:08:29,394 --> 00:08:32,279
It's a long weekend next week.

125
00:08:32,279 --> 00:08:35,580
And isn't your Visa still active?

126
00:08:35,580 --> 00:08:37,260
Slow down, Guys.

127
00:08:37,260 --> 00:08:40,571
I just got home. Where are you taking me?

128
00:08:40,571 --> 00:08:44,035
I also need to check if I am available.

129
00:08:44,035 --> 00:08:47,258
Come on, Fah. It isn't like we get to travel together very often.

130
00:08:47,258 --> 00:08:51,512
You can take the one from the mountain with you.

131
00:09:01,739 --> 00:09:03,776
Are you okay, Fah?

132
00:09:05,167 --> 00:09:07,167
It's nothing.

133
00:09:07,167 --> 00:09:09,288
It's just that we don't talk anymore.

134
00:09:12,404 --> 00:09:15,212
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

135
00:09:15,212 --> 00:09:18,698
Why did you two stop talking?

136
00:09:22,108 --> 00:09:24,508
Things just didn't really work out.

137
00:09:24,508 --> 00:09:27,579
Forget it. Let's not talk about it.

138
00:09:27,579 --> 00:09:30,985
Let's just continue drinking.

139
00:09:30,985 --> 00:09:33,735
Here. Let me refill it for you.

140
00:09:37,836 --> 00:09:40,125
Maybe refill for yourself first.

141
00:10:16,763 --> 00:10:22,205
Actually, it's for you, but many things happened.

142
00:10:26,984 --> 00:10:28,884
Well then,

143
00:10:29,999 --> 00:10:32,660
can I just give it to you now?

144
00:10:37,240 --> 00:10:39,948
You must get well soon.

145
00:10:39,948 --> 00:10:42,122
After your recovery,

146
00:10:43,161 --> 00:10:46,041
I have something for you as well.

147
00:10:47,453 --> 00:10:49,437
Of course.

148
00:11:25,004 --> 00:11:27,900
[One Month Later]

149
00:11:27,900 --> 00:11:29,900
- How are you?
- I'm doing well.

150
00:11:31,567 --> 00:11:35,622
Fah, I'd like to trade shifts with you this Saturday.

151
00:11:35,622 --> 00:11:38,948
You sent someone to talk to me earlier, right?

152
00:11:38,948 --> 00:11:40,202
You got it.

153
00:11:40,202 --> 00:11:41,551
All right. Thank you so much.

154
00:11:41,551 --> 00:11:43,759
Sure. My pleasure.

155
00:11:43,759 --> 00:11:45,662
Hey.

156
00:11:45,662 --> 00:11:47,416
Seriously, what did you eat?

157
00:11:47,416 --> 00:11:48,709
You're so energetic.

158
00:11:48,709 --> 00:11:54,140
I finally got back to work. I want to do my best.

159
00:11:54,140 --> 00:11:57,449
Don't just work. Find someone to take care of you.

160
00:11:57,449 --> 00:12:02,017
People in our profession have a hard time finding a lover.

161
00:12:02,017 --> 00:12:05,946
Maybe I'm better off alone.

162
00:12:05,946 --> 00:12:07,190
Please excuse me.

163
00:12:07,190 --> 00:12:08,639
Of course.

164
00:12:08,639 --> 00:12:10,884
Wow!

165
00:12:10,884 --> 00:12:13,640
You all did so well today.

166
00:12:13,640 --> 00:12:16,513
I'm sure the real event will be just spectacular.

167
00:12:16,513 --> 00:12:17,763
You all did well today.

168
00:12:17,763 --> 00:12:21,083
Everyone can go home and rest now.

169
00:12:35,593 --> 00:12:36,796
Prince, Dear.

170
00:12:36,796 --> 00:12:39,104
Actually, since I'm here to get a medical check-up today,

171
00:12:39,104 --> 00:12:41,779
you should get one, too.

172
00:12:41,779 --> 00:12:45,903
That's all right. I'll get it some other time.

173
00:12:48,635 --> 00:12:51,501
I don't think there's a problem.

174
00:12:51,501 --> 00:12:53,201
Of course.

175
00:13:17,211 --> 00:13:20,001
Coming to the hospital reminds me of Dr. Fah, doesn't it?

176
00:13:20,001 --> 00:13:22,848
Do you still keep in touch with Dr. Fah?

177
00:13:23,672 --> 00:13:25,219
No, I don't.

178
00:13:25,219 --> 00:13:27,336
Why not?

179
00:13:28,168 --> 00:13:32,297
I got his number from the Village Headman, but I can't reach him no matter how many times I've called.

180
00:13:32,297 --> 00:13:35,709
He probably changed it.

181
00:13:35,709 --> 00:13:38,060
Do you want me to help find Dr. Fah's phone number?

182
00:13:38,060 --> 00:13:41,574
I'm sure he wants to reach out to you as well.

183
00:13:41,574 --> 00:13:45,429
If he did, he would have called long ago.

184
00:13:45,429 --> 00:13:48,968
Maybe he doesn't have your number, either.

185
00:13:51,362 --> 00:13:54,128
If he called the Village Headman he would have gotten it right away.

186
00:13:54,128 --> 00:13:55,532
Never mind him.

187
00:13:55,532 --> 00:14:00,410
He's probably so busy with work that he's forgotten me already.

188
00:14:00,410 --> 00:14:02,490
Let's go, the elevator is here.

189
00:15:05,874 --> 00:15:07,474
Fah.

190
00:15:09,220 --> 00:15:11,553
There's a letter for you.

191
00:15:11,553 --> 00:15:12,917
The credit card company?

192
00:15:12,917 --> 00:15:15,755
I think I just paid them.

193
00:15:15,755 --> 00:15:20,332
No. Look. It says here that it was sent from the mountain.

194
00:15:20,332 --> 00:15:21,832
Really?

195
00:15:32,173 --> 00:15:35,186
They've invited me to the ceremony for the donations of medical supplies.

196
00:15:35,186 --> 00:15:36,560
Wait.

197
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,575
Why would they invite you?

198
00:15:38,575 --> 00:15:43,418
Because I was the one who filed the request for the supplies.

199
00:15:43,418 --> 00:15:47,874
Do you know how hard it is to make the request?

200
00:15:49,028 --> 00:15:51,469
What a good heart you have.

201
00:15:51,469 --> 00:15:53,117
Are you going?

202
00:16:00,220 --> 00:16:02,377
I don't think I can.

203
00:16:02,977 --> 00:16:04,596
I have work to do here.

204
00:16:04,596 --> 00:16:06,001
Yes?

205
00:16:06,001 --> 00:16:10,291
It's not because you don't have the guts to see the teacher up there?

206
00:16:10,291 --> 00:16:13,991
Hold on. How did you know about this?

207
00:16:14,854 --> 00:16:18,505
P'JJ and P'Mesa told me everything.

208
00:16:18,505 --> 00:16:20,834
I think you should go.

209
00:16:20,834 --> 00:16:24,273
At least you will get to say a proper goodbye.

210
00:16:24,273 --> 00:16:26,504
Otherwise, you'll have unfinished matters.

211
00:16:48,999 --> 00:16:50,912
- Hello, Loong Phang.
- Hello.

212
00:16:50,912 --> 00:16:54,230
I didn't think I would get to see you again this soon.

213
00:16:54,230 --> 00:16:58,503
It's my day off, so I thought I should visit.

214
00:16:58,503 --> 00:16:59,803
Sure.

215
00:17:27,317 --> 00:17:29,885
Khun, I brought some vitamin C for the chil—

216
00:17:29,885 --> 00:17:31,644
Oh.

217
00:17:31,644 --> 00:17:33,984
Khru Prince went to the restroom.

218
00:17:37,030 --> 00:17:39,503
And what are you guys drawing?

219
00:17:39,503 --> 00:17:42,556
Khru Prince told us to draw whatever we liked.

220
00:17:44,893 --> 00:17:48,126
Viah, do you have some paper and colored pencils for me?

221
00:17:48,126 --> 00:17:51,310
- I do.
- May I borrow them?

222
00:17:58,690 --> 00:18:01,400
Have you guys finished?

223
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,785
We are done.

224
00:18:10,621 --> 00:18:13,702
If you're finished, hand it to me.

225
00:18:21,682 --> 00:18:23,932
This is my assignment, Khru.

226
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:26,886
What are you doing?

227
00:18:26,886 --> 00:18:31,094
I'm handing in the assignment you gave,

228
00:18:31,094 --> 00:18:33,591
to draw whatever I like.

229
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:06,900
[By Prince]

230
00:19:09,356 --> 00:19:10,920
Hey.

231
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:14,371
Why are you here alone?

232
00:19:18,658 --> 00:19:20,972
Didn't Khru Prince come up with you?

233
00:19:20,972 --> 00:19:24,962
I wanted return him the tote bag he forgot.

234
00:19:24,962 --> 00:19:27,718
After we both went home, we never contacted each other.

235
00:19:27,718 --> 00:19:32,093
Why? Did you fight?

236
00:19:34,028 --> 00:19:36,021
Not exactly.

237
00:19:36,021 --> 00:19:40,988
I think there is someone who can take better care of him than I can.

238
00:19:40,988 --> 00:19:42,419
Gosh!

239
00:19:42,419 --> 00:19:46,276
What? Are you giving up already?

240
00:19:47,066 --> 00:19:50,230
I've thought it through, Yayah.

241
00:19:50,230 --> 00:19:52,204
Do you know what?

242
00:19:52,204 --> 00:19:57,159
Nong Pangam was going to make a more beautiful and bigger bag for Khru Prince.

243
00:19:57,159 --> 00:20:01,020
But he didn't want it. Do you know why?

244
00:20:02,617 --> 00:20:04,767
His reason was simple.

245
00:20:04,767 --> 00:20:07,187
He said he just liked this embroidery.

246
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:11,337
Life is that simple.

247
00:20:11,337 --> 00:20:15,958
Sometimes, you don't need reasons to like something.

248
00:20:19,600 --> 00:20:23,640
But… I think it's too late, Yayah.

249
00:20:25,337 --> 00:20:28,126
He probably has a new tote bag now.

250
00:20:38,860 --> 00:20:40,740
[Domestic Departures]
[International Departures]

251
00:21:01,920 --> 00:21:04,358
Did you just get back from the mountain?

252
00:21:08,331 --> 00:21:10,076
Yes.

253
00:21:10,076 --> 00:21:12,567
You look disappointed somehow.

254
00:21:12,567 --> 00:21:15,387
I guess you didn't see who you wanted to see.

255
00:21:17,419 --> 00:21:19,633
I went to Chiang Mai...

256
00:21:20,871 --> 00:21:24,155
hoping to see Khru Prince. That's all.

257
00:21:24,155 --> 00:21:30,589
I wanted to know if he's happy under your care.

258
00:21:30,589 --> 00:21:33,050
You don't need to ask.

259
00:21:33,050 --> 00:21:35,147
I don't have to take care of patients.

260
00:21:35,147 --> 00:21:39,775
I have time for Prince when he needs it.

261
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:47,144
Even so,

262
00:21:47,144 --> 00:21:50,077
he doesn't seem happy.

263
00:21:51,575 --> 00:21:54,077
Unlike when he was with you.

264
00:21:54,796 --> 00:21:57,990
I know I don't have the right to say this.

265
00:21:58,935 --> 00:22:02,072
I just want Prince to meet a good person.

266
00:22:02,072 --> 00:22:04,897
Someone who can take care of him.

267
00:22:07,492 --> 00:22:11,311
From now on, please take care of him.

268
00:22:29,708 --> 00:22:31,314
Hello.

269
00:22:31,314 --> 00:22:34,160
I don't think I can take your shift tonight.

270
00:22:35,090 --> 00:22:37,134
I'm going to Chiang Mai.

271
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,054
Khru Prince! Are you home?

272
00:22:53,054 --> 00:22:56,253
Khru Prince! Khru Prince!

273
00:23:02,288 --> 00:23:04,009
Oh, Khun Kuafah.

274
00:23:04,009 --> 00:23:06,743
Hello. Is Khru Prince home?

275
00:23:06,743 --> 00:23:09,968
I must apologize, there is nobody home at the moment.

276
00:23:09,968 --> 00:23:13,880
Khru Prince's family is traveling to Germany right now.

277
00:23:15,307 --> 00:23:17,317
Germany?

278
00:23:35,914 --> 00:23:37,614
Seriously, Fah?

279
00:23:39,042 --> 00:23:42,452
Yes. I've made up my mind.

280
00:23:42,452 --> 00:23:45,696
It's Germany, Phi. Not Siam.

281
00:23:49,319 --> 00:23:52,830
I've kept him waiting for me long enough.

282
00:23:52,830 --> 00:23:56,315
I don't want him to wait any longer.

283
00:23:58,361 --> 00:24:00,161
Let's go then.

284
00:24:17,071 --> 00:24:21,450
Prince? I'm already at the airport.

285
00:24:22,803 --> 00:24:24,298
That's okay.

286
00:24:24,298 --> 00:24:28,379
I should be the one who feels bad for missing your event as a drum major,

287
00:24:28,379 --> 00:24:31,667
but I know you're great. You will nail it.

288
00:24:31,667 --> 00:24:32,815
Keep fighting!

289
00:24:32,815 --> 00:24:36,579
Don't forget to record the video for me to watch later.

290
00:24:36,579 --> 00:24:37,820
Sure.

291
00:24:37,820 --> 00:24:39,505
I'll see you.

292
00:24:39,505 --> 00:24:41,305
Bye bye.

293
00:25:15,420 --> 00:25:17,660
[Trintara University]

294
00:25:22,150 --> 00:25:23,544
Wow!

295
00:25:23,544 --> 00:25:26,345
And that was our opening parade.

296
00:25:26,345 --> 00:25:28,359
It was just gorgeous. Right, everyone?

297
00:25:28,359 --> 00:25:31,674
Let's give it up for them!

298
00:25:45,323 --> 00:25:46,623
Here.

299
00:26:04,420 --> 00:26:06,123
What are you doing?

300
00:26:06,123 --> 00:26:09,363
I'm taking you traveling, but you're messing with me.

301
00:26:11,050 --> 00:26:13,358
I just bought you a drink

302
00:26:13,358 --> 00:26:16,358
as a thank you for taking me out.

303
00:26:42,346 --> 00:26:43,512
Excuse me.

304
00:26:43,512 --> 00:26:47,294
Guys, is anyone there named Prince?

305
00:26:47,294 --> 00:26:49,657
There's someone asking for you.

306
00:26:49,657 --> 00:26:52,047
Prince? Prince? Nong Prince?

307
00:26:52,047 --> 00:26:53,543
Hey! Nong Prince!

308
00:26:53,543 --> 00:26:55,405
Someone is looking for you.

309
00:26:55,405 --> 00:26:57,105
Over there.

310
00:27:08,296 --> 00:27:10,096
Prince!

311
00:27:11,685 --> 00:27:14,294
Prince! You wait right there.

312
00:27:14,294 --> 00:27:16,036
Okay.

313
00:27:16,036 --> 00:27:17,786
That's great, Phi—

314
00:27:22,229 --> 00:27:23,654
Go.

315
00:27:23,654 --> 00:27:25,020
I'll walk you.

316
00:27:25,020 --> 00:27:28,693
Come on, let's go.

317
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:43,700
How did you get here?

318
00:27:51,119 --> 00:27:54,226
We have an hour before we can check in.

319
00:27:55,916 --> 00:27:58,183
So that's the story.

320
00:27:58,183 --> 00:27:59,613
Wow!

321
00:27:59,613 --> 00:28:01,475
That's so damn cool!

322
00:28:01,475 --> 00:28:03,105
Falling in love with the teacher up on the mountain.

323
00:28:03,105 --> 00:28:05,196
And traveling to Germany to look for him.

324
00:28:05,196 --> 00:28:08,820
It's more romantic than a movie!

325
00:28:08,820 --> 00:28:11,240
Can you guys not encourage him like that?

326
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:14,012
Trust me. You can never find him.

327
00:28:14,012 --> 00:28:16,947
By the way, your story sounds familiar.

328
00:28:16,947 --> 00:28:19,201
It's like my friend's story.

329
00:28:19,201 --> 00:28:24,015
He said when he was a teacher up on the mountain, he got his heart broken by the doctor there.

330
00:28:24,015 --> 00:28:26,320
- Really?
- Yes.

331
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:29,665
So many coincidences in this world.

332
00:28:31,041 --> 00:28:36,508
Your friend doesn't happen to be named Prince, right?

333
00:28:39,075 --> 00:28:42,359
How did you know that?

334
00:28:42,359 --> 00:28:43,677
Wait a minute.

335
00:28:43,677 --> 00:28:49,991
Does your friend Prince have the last name of the northern monarch?

336
00:28:50,810 --> 00:28:52,757
Bullseye!

337
00:28:52,757 --> 00:28:54,475
That's correct, Phi!

338
00:28:54,475 --> 00:28:56,045
How did you know that?

339
00:28:56,045 --> 00:28:58,056
For real?

340
00:28:58,056 --> 00:29:00,501
Is this world really that small?

341
00:29:00,501 --> 00:29:02,475
It's not just small, Fah.

342
00:29:02,475 --> 00:29:04,716
Prince is also my and Kluen's friend.

343
00:29:04,716 --> 00:29:05,741
What?

344
00:29:05,741 --> 00:29:07,571
Wait, let's not get into that.

345
00:29:07,571 --> 00:29:10,495
Ai Prince isn't in Germany right now.

346
00:29:10,495 --> 00:29:12,893
He's a drum major right now at his university.

347
00:29:12,893 --> 00:29:14,593
That's right, Fah.

348
00:29:16,381 --> 00:29:18,515
Then, let me excuse myself.

349
00:29:18,515 --> 00:29:21,222
- What?
- Wait...

350
00:29:21,222 --> 00:29:23,434
Is the world so small?

351
00:29:23,434 --> 00:29:24,571
Keep going, Fah!

352
00:29:24,571 --> 00:29:26,569
Find him!

353
00:29:26,569 --> 00:29:28,681
Fighting!

354
00:29:30,911 --> 00:29:33,104
That's why I am right here.

355
00:29:35,113 --> 00:29:38,941
So… why do you want to see me?

356
00:29:39,857 --> 00:29:42,137
I got something for you.

357
00:29:46,634 --> 00:29:51,465
I chose the pink stone that brings good luck in love

358
00:29:51,465 --> 00:29:55,009
so our love will go smoothly.

359
00:29:55,009 --> 00:29:58,454
Aw!

360
00:29:58,454 --> 00:30:00,354
Let me put it on for you.

361
00:30:34,694 --> 00:30:35,878
Will you be my boyfriend?

362
00:30:35,878 --> 00:30:39,278
Say yes, say yes, say yes...

363
00:30:49,792 --> 00:30:51,988
What are you even saying?

364
00:30:52,767 --> 00:30:55,113
What do you say?

365
00:30:55,113 --> 00:30:56,840
Yes! Yes! Yes!

366
00:31:00,150 --> 00:31:01,540
Yes.

367
00:31:12,184 --> 00:31:14,365
Don't leave me again.

368
00:31:16,518 --> 00:31:20,579
Even if someone chases me away, I won't leave.

369
00:31:44,848 --> 00:31:46,800
What are you doing?

370
00:31:47,627 --> 00:31:50,582
Why? Because we're in public?

371
00:31:50,582 --> 00:31:52,799
Do you think I care?

372
00:31:56,040 --> 00:31:57,740
Let's go.

373
00:32:18,835 --> 00:32:20,708
Hello.

374
00:32:20,708 --> 00:32:23,129
I didn't think we would meet again so soon for another round.

375
00:32:23,129 --> 00:32:26,007
But this time you have more people.

376
00:32:42,419 --> 00:32:44,415
Khru Prince!

377
00:32:46,230 --> 00:32:50,740
♫ Do you think love is still waiting for you ♫

378
00:32:50,740 --> 00:32:56,670
♫ Did you know I once gave up ♫

379
00:32:56,670 --> 00:32:59,590
♫ How much I've cried for love ♫

380
00:32:59,590 --> 00:33:01,550
Come here!

381
00:33:01,550 --> 00:33:06,430
♫ Taking a journey, no matter how far the horizon ♫

382
00:33:06,433 --> 00:33:09,820
Khru Prince, I made this for you.

383
00:33:09,820 --> 00:33:17,660
♫ But in the end, it's too late, love vanished ♫

384
00:33:38,660 --> 00:33:40,970
Move out of the way!

385
00:33:40,972 --> 00:33:43,737
Tell me. How much is 1+1?

386
00:33:43,737 --> 00:33:45,050
Two.

387
00:33:45,050 --> 00:33:46,664
And 2+2?

388
00:33:46,664 --> 00:33:49,187
Four.

389
00:33:49,187 --> 00:33:51,470
And what is P'Kluen plus P'Dao?

390
00:33:51,470 --> 00:33:53,730
Boyfriends.

391
00:33:53,730 --> 00:34:00,980
♫ Do you think that our love really exists? ♫

392
00:34:21,151 --> 00:34:22,646
- I…
- I…

393
00:34:22,646 --> 00:34:24,946
have something for you.

394
00:34:26,175 --> 00:34:28,787
You made it for me too?

395
00:34:28,787 --> 00:34:30,412
Yes.

396
00:34:30,412 --> 00:34:32,480
I'll put it on for you.

397
00:34:35,130 --> 00:34:38,380
♫ Nobody on this earth ♫

398
00:34:38,380 --> 00:34:44,280
♫ Finds one true love right from the start ♫

399
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:47,490
♫ Everyone on this earth ♫

400
00:34:47,490 --> 00:34:52,460
♫ Has their share of broken hearts ♫

401
00:34:52,460 --> 00:35:00,444
♫ I know how scary this is ♫
♫ I feel it, too, like shots in the dark ♫

402
00:35:00,444 --> 00:35:02,548
It's chilly up here.

403
00:35:05,888 --> 00:35:09,069
You've been warned to wear warmer clothes.

404
00:35:09,069 --> 00:35:11,475
You are just stubborn.

405
00:35:11,475 --> 00:35:14,739
Stubborn, but still cute, right?

406
00:35:32,158 --> 00:35:33,758
Is it better?

407
00:35:35,905 --> 00:35:37,505
Thank you.

408
00:35:50,447 --> 00:35:52,047
Did you know?

409
00:35:52,767 --> 00:35:58,741
I used to be so afraid to climb the Himalayas.

410
00:36:02,043 --> 00:36:04,143
The Himalayas?

411
00:36:04,143 --> 00:36:06,618
It's a metaphor.

412
00:36:07,990 --> 00:36:12,693
I compare the Himalayas to life achievement.

413
00:36:14,929 --> 00:36:20,127
I used to dream of climbing the Himalayas with someone.

414
00:36:21,893 --> 00:36:24,683
After my ex and I broke up,

415
00:36:25,416 --> 00:36:28,485
I've been so afraid to climb it.

416
00:36:32,549 --> 00:36:34,049
But now,

417
00:36:35,592 --> 00:36:37,886
I'm not afraid anymore.

418
00:36:41,554 --> 00:36:43,154
Why?

419
00:36:45,087 --> 00:36:46,487
Well...

420
00:36:47,730 --> 00:36:50,634
I have you to climb it with me.

421
00:37:05,649 --> 00:37:09,501
Please stay and climb the mountain with me for a long time,

422
00:37:09,501 --> 00:37:11,201
Khru Prince.

423
00:37:19,184 --> 00:37:21,450
You're sure, right?

424
00:37:22,571 --> 00:37:25,841
That you will be my Prince.

425
00:37:27,276 --> 00:37:28,876
No.

426
00:37:32,890 --> 00:37:36,060
It's you who must be mine.

427
00:37:42,942 --> 00:37:47,080
Are you ready, my Kuafah?

428
00:37:48,124 --> 00:37:49,724
Bring it on.

429
00:37:50,580 --> 00:37:54,010
♫ Please let me be the North Star ♫

430
00:37:54,010 --> 00:37:58,220
♫ To guide your heart ♫

431
00:37:58,220 --> 00:38:03,470
♫ To be next to mine, like the sky and starlight ♫

